Bottom Line:
Yes, use a dedicated Settings page because:
✅ Better organization - All settings in one place
✅ More space - Can show complex options clearly
✅ Easier navigation - Clear URL structure
✅ Future-proof - Can add more settings easily
✅ Mobile-friendly - Works well on all devices
The settings should be easily accessible from the main dashboard navigation, and changes should immediately affect the rest of the application (schedules, employees, reports, etc.).

